│ THOUGHT: The SLP vectorizer narrows integer bitwidth and constructs vector operations using that MinBW. In this bug, it narrows to i1 and then builds a vector icmp on <N x i1>, leading │
│ to poison differences. A safe fix is to clamp the narrowed integer bitwidth to at least 8 bits when materializing types, preventing creation of <N x i1> vectors. I will modify the code │
│ where it uses MinBW to build IntegerType::get(..., MinBW) to instead use max(MinBW, 8).                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
