│ icmp when the compared scalar type is i1 — fall back to gathering in that case. I will modify the ICmp handling in SLPVectorizer.cpp to check if the compared type is 1-bit integer and, │
│ if so, return NeedToGather instead of Vectorize. This prevents emitting <N x i1> icmp vectors while minimally impacting other cases.                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '7679,7688s/return TreeEntry::Vectorize;/if (ComparedTy->isIntegerTy(1)) { LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Avoid vectorizing icmp on i1 to prevent poison propagation.\\n"); return    │
│ TreeEntry::NeedToGather; } return TreeEntry::Vectorize;/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                                │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
