│ conservative, targeted fix is to avoid vectorizing trunc when the destination element type is i1: fall back to gathering for such cases. This prevents producing <N x i1> vectors in the │
│ first place while minimally impacting other transformations.                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '7666a \ \ \ \ \ \ if (auto *DstITy = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(VL0->getType())) { if (DstITy->getBitWidth() == 1) { LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Avoid vectorizing trunc to i1 to      │
│ prevent poison propagation.\\n"); return TreeEntry::NeedToGather; } }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
